- Here we are.
- 20 years down the road.

44
00:04:56,570 --> 00:04:58,197
－是的
－這有點奇怪
- Yeah.
- It's kind of odd.

45
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:00,825
一切是怎麼開始的？
我從沒有機會問這個
How did it come to you?
Like, I never... I would never guess

46
00:05:00,908 --> 00:05:02,368
比如，你怎麼會執導哈利波特？
to ask this question, how did you
end up doing Harry Potter?

47
00:05:02,451 --> 00:05:04,578
我這樣做是因為
我的女兒，艾莉諾
I ended up doing it
because my daughter, Eleanor

48
00:05:04,662 --> 00:05:06,414
說服我讀那些書
convinced me to read the books
after I refused three times.

49
00:05:06,497 --> 00:05:08,249
－在我拒絕了三次之後
－好的

50
00:05:08,332 --> 00:05:10,000
「阿茲卡班的逃犯」一推出
So once Prisoner of Azkaban came out

51
00:05:10,084 --> 00:05:11,460
－我說…
－謝謝你，艾莉諾
- Thank you, Eleanor.
- I said... I said

52
00:05:11,544 --> 00:05:15,005
我說「好，我終於可以讀了」
"Okay, I'll read these finally."

53
00:05:15,089 --> 00:05:18,050
緊接著我得知要開拍電影
And then immediately,
I saw the movies.

54
00:05:18,134 --> 00:05:19,552
這是前所未有的狀況
I just saw them,
And that hasn't happened since.

55
00:05:19,635 --> 00:05:23,931
然後我飛到愛丁堡去見ＪＫ羅琳
Then I had to fly to Edinburgh
to meet Jo Rowling.

56
00:05:24,014 --> 00:05:26,475
基本上就是跟她說
「這是我的願景」
And essentially said,
"This is my vision."

57
00:05:26,559 --> 00:05:28,519
她說「這正是我看電影的方式」
She said, "That's exactly
the way I see the movie."

58
00:05:29,395 --> 00:05:30,813
當書出版的時候
When the books came out,
the queues of kids around the block

59
00:05:30,896 --> 00:05:32,523
街區的孩子們排起了長長的隊伍

60
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:34,275
{\an5}（羅比寇特蘭，飾魯霸海格）
I mean, thousands of them
all waiting for their letters run.

61
00:05:34,358 --> 00:05:36,777
{\an5}成千上萬的人
正在等待最新的出版

62
00:05:36,861 --> 00:05:38,279
（哈利波特：死神的聖物Ｉ）

63
00:05:40,656 --> 00:05:44,535
{\an5}很多人開始愛上ＪＫ羅琳的作品
So many people were beginning
to fall in love

64
00:05:42,908 --> 00:05:44,076
with J.K. Rowling's writing.

65
00:05:44,618 --> 00:05:47,204
我那時大概八歲
I think I probably would've been
about eight years old.

66
00:05:47,288 --> 00:05:49,665
{\an5}那是第一集出來的時候
I think that's when the first one
came out.

67
00:05:49,749 --> 00:05:51,834
就像融入了我們的家庭一樣
It became like our family thing.

68
00:05:51,917 --> 00:05:53,544
我爸爸模仿過所有的聲音
My dad used to do all the voices

69
00:05:53,627 --> 00:05:56,380
我和我弟變得痴迷
and my brother and I
just became obsessed.

70
00:05:56,464 --> 00:05:58,591
我們求他繼續唸
We would just beg him to keep going.

71
00:05:58,674 --> 00:06:02,678
每當他唸一章，我們都會說
「再來一章，拜託？」
And every time he'd finish a chapter,
we'd be like

72
00:06:00,509 --> 00:06:02,219
"One more! One more!
Please, just one more.

73
00:06:02,762 --> 00:06:04,096
「再一章」
Please, please, please.
One more, one more, one more."

74
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:07,266
我在學校的一個朋友
有前兩集的書
A friend of mine at school had
the first two.

75
00:06:07,349 --> 00:06:08,934
我去他家過夜
I went for a sleepover at his house.

76
00:06:09,018 --> 00:06:11,562
{\an5}他說「神祕的魔法石」在書架上
He said, "Well, Philosopher's Stone's
there on the bookshelf."

77
00:06:11,645 --> 00:06:14,064
我們開始徹夜讀書
That's what we did
this whole sleepover.

78
00:06:14,148 --> 00:06:16,692
我們靜靜地坐在那裡
他在讀「消失的密室」
We just both sat there in silence,
him reading Chamber of Secrets

79
00:06:16,776 --> 00:06:18,360
我在讀「神祕的魔法石」
me reading Philosopher's Stone.

80
00:06:18,444 --> 00:06:19,945
我讀到無法自拔
And that was it, really.
I never looked back.

81
00:06:20,029 --> 00:06:23,282
{\an5}我在閱讀的過程
瞬間和弗雷德和喬治產生共鳴
At the time of reading

82
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,157
we instantly related
to Fred and George

83
00:06:23,365 --> 00:06:25,159
{\an5}因為文學作品中沒有多少雙胞胎
because there aren't many twins
in literature.

84
00:06:25,242 --> 00:06:29,955
{\an5}「消失的密室」
是我第一本熬夜在看的書
The Chamber of Secrets
was the first book

85
00:06:26,744 --> 00:06:29,914
that I sort of genuinely stayed up
at night reading.

86
00:06:30,039 --> 00:06:31,707
文筆真生動
The writing was so vivid.

87
00:06:31,791 --> 00:06:34,084
人物關係如此融洽
The characters so relatable.

88
00:06:34,168 --> 00:06:37,213
{\an5}這是一個如此錯綜複雜的
It was such an intricately,
perfectly designed universe.

89
00:06:37,296 --> 00:06:39,256
完美設計的宇宙

90
00:06:39,340 --> 00:06:40,841
我覺得當時很容易忘記
I think it's very easy to forget
that at the time

91
00:06:40,925 --> 00:06:43,385
{\an5}人們都在談論閱讀是無趣的
people were talking about, like,
the death of reading.

92
00:06:43,469 --> 00:06:46,597
{\an5}我只是覺得這是美妙的人生觀
I just think it's a beautiful,
creative outlook on life

93
00:06:46,680 --> 00:06:48,474
這種對無限可能的信念
this belief
in limitless possibilities.

94
00:06:48,557 --> 00:06:51,185
我非常欣賞
ＪＫ羅琳的眾多原因之一
One of the many reasons I admire
J.K. so much

95
00:06:51,268 --> 00:06:53,562
是數百萬人正在讀書
is that millions would now read books

96
00:06:53,646 --> 00:06:55,940
或許他們這輩子
都不會拿起一本書
who would never have lifted
a book up in their lives.

97
00:06:56,023 --> 00:06:58,943
而你突然意識到寫作的力量
And you suddenly realize
the power of writing.

98
00:06:59,026 --> 00:07:00,319
哈利
Hip, hip, Harry!

99
00:07:00,402 --> 00:07:03,447
然後在選角方面，這是…
And then in terms of casting

100
00:07:02,321 --> 00:07:06,826
it was the search for Harry Potter,
it was insane.

101
00:07:03,531 --> 00:07:06,826
尋找哈利波特的過程很瘋狂

102
00:07:06,909 --> 00:07:09,453
新的「哈利波特」電影
正在尋找孩子
The new Harry Potter film are
looking for children

103
00:07:09,537 --> 00:07:13,541
在這部價值數百萬鎊的電影中
飾演三個主要角色
to play the three main roles
in the multi-million pound film.

104
00:07:15,251 --> 00:07:17,545
我記得第一次去試鏡
I remember going
to the... the very first audition

105
00:07:17,628 --> 00:07:21,090
有數百甚至數千人
and there were hundreds,
if not thousands of people.

106
00:07:21,173 --> 00:07:23,425
然後我們意識到
我們是那裡唯一的一對
And then we realized that we were
the only set of twins there

107
00:07:23,509 --> 00:07:25,052
沒有穿相同衣服的雙胞胎
who weren't wearing
identical clothing

108
00:07:25,135 --> 00:07:27,137
所以我們越過馬路
so we ended up going over the road

109
00:07:27,221 --> 00:07:30,474
買了兩件相同的上衣
and bought two identical,
matching tops.

110
00:07:30,558 --> 00:07:31,892
－直接穿上
－直接穿上
- Just off the rack.
- Just off the rack.

111
00:07:31,976 --> 00:07:33,686
拿了就走
They're like, "Right, they will do."
And then off we went.

112
00:07:33,769 --> 00:07:36,021
他們讓所有人集合
They'd let us all mill, you know,
sort of congregate.

113
00:07:36,105 --> 00:07:37,356
聚集在一起

114
00:07:37,439 --> 00:07:39,733
{\an5}所以他們似乎走開了
So they seemingly walked away.

115
00:07:39,817 --> 00:07:43,904
{\an5}還有一個男生拿著麥克風
舉在我們的頭上
And of course,
while there's still one gentleman

116
00:07:41,068 --> 00:07:43,821
holding a boom mic
straight over our heads.

117
00:07:43,988 --> 00:07:46,991
有個小女孩問我「那是什麼？」
And this little girl asks me,
"What's that?"

118
00:07:48,242 --> 00:07:50,578
我說「看就知道是麥克風啊」
I think I even said,
"It's a mic. Duh."

119
00:07:51,412 --> 00:07:53,873
「他們正在拍攝
是在測試我們」
And I was like, "They're filming us.
This is just like a trick."

120
00:07:53,956 --> 00:07:55,749
「我以前也有參與過」
Like, as if I've done it before,
really.

121
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:57,376
我記得，因為問的人就是艾瑪
I remember it because it was Emma.

122
00:07:57,459 --> 00:08:02,339
我徹底被這次試鏡的
興奮氛圍所吸引
I became completely gripped

123
00:07:59,086 --> 00:08:02,298
by the excitement
around this audition.

124
00:08:02,423 --> 00:08:05,718
我的目標就是拿下妙麗的角色
I always knew
that I was going for Hermione

125
00:08:05,801 --> 00:08:09,263
我的堅持讓我父母很擔心
他們想說…
in a way, that I think,
terrified my parents

126
00:08:07,761 --> 00:08:09,263
because they were like

127
00:08:09,346 --> 00:08:11,932
「如果她沒有得到這個角色
我們該怎麼辦？」
"What are we gonna do with her
if she doesn't get the part?"

128
00:08:12,016 --> 00:08:13,058
我很興奮
I was just excited.
I wasn't sort of daunted.

129
00:08:13,142 --> 00:08:15,477
我並沒有被嚇倒，沒思考太多

130
00:08:14,476 --> 00:08:16,937
I wasn't thinking, "I wonder
how many films they're gonna make."

131
00:08:15,561 --> 00:08:17,771
我想知道他們要拍多少部電影

132
00:08:17,855 --> 00:08:19,106
我想「這會很有趣」
Anything like that.
I thought, oh, this will be fun.

133
00:08:19,189 --> 00:08:21,025
{\an5}我覺得一開始最大的壓力
And I think the biggest pressure
at the beginning was

134
00:08:21,108 --> 00:08:22,359
{\an5}是誰將成為哈利波特
who was gonna be Harry Potter.

135
00:08:22,443 --> 00:08:25,779
我們找不到哈利
We couldn't find Harry.

136
00:08:24,028 --> 00:08:25,988
We couldn't.
We just couldn't find Harry.

137
00:08:25,863 --> 00:08:28,991
情況變得有點奇怪
大家也開始緊張起來
And it was getting kind of weird
and panicky.

138
00:08:29,074 --> 00:08:32,912
有一天晚上
我在倫敦的酒店房間裡
I was in my hotel room
in London one night

139
00:08:32,995 --> 00:08:35,039
觀看電台的「大衛高帕菲」
watching the BBC version
of David Copperfield.

140
00:08:35,122 --> 00:08:36,999
我突然靈光一閃
Immediately, a light bulb went off
in my head and I said

141
00:08:37,082 --> 00:08:38,751
「這就是哈利波特」
"This is Harry Potter.

142
00:08:38,834 --> 00:08:41,545
「這就是我們幾個月來
一直在尋找的孩子」
This is the kid we've been
looking for, for months."

143
00:08:41,629 --> 00:08:43,422
所以我問了選角導演，我說…
So I asked the casting director
and I said

144
00:08:43,505 --> 00:08:45,507
「我們必須讓他來這裡試鏡」
"We've got to get him in here
for an audition."

145
00:08:45,591 --> 00:08:46,842
她說「這根本不可能」
She said, "It's never gonna happen.

146
00:08:46,926 --> 00:08:50,095
「他父母不想讓他捲入演藝圈」
His parents do not want him
involved in this world.

147
00:08:50,179 --> 00:08:51,597
「他們不希望他飾演這個角色」
They don't want him
to take this role."

148
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:54,141
合約是簽所有七部電影
I think the deal was
to sign on for all seven films

149
00:08:54,224 --> 00:08:55,726
他們將在洛杉磯拍攝
and they would be filmed in LA,
so Mom and Dad were like

150
00:08:55,809 --> 00:08:58,854
爸媽認為「這對他的生活來說
是一個巨大的干擾」
"No, that's like a huge disruption
to his life."

151
00:08:58,938 --> 00:09:04,026
幸運的是
幾週後大衛海曼去了劇院
Fortunately, David Hayman went
to the theater a few weeks later.

152
00:09:04,109 --> 00:09:07,071
排在我前面的這兩個傢伙轉身
These two guys in the row
in front of me

153
00:09:05,819 --> 00:09:07,029
started sort of turning round.

154
00:09:07,154 --> 00:09:09,490
大衛是偉大的製作人
David being the great producer
that he is

155
00:09:09,573 --> 00:09:14,453
說服丹的父親帶丹參加試鏡
convinced Dan's father
to bring Dan in for an audition.

156
00:09:13,369 --> 00:09:17,164
And that's basically
when we got our Harry Potter.

157
00:09:14,536 --> 00:09:17,206
基本上就是
我們選定哈利波特的時候

158
00:09:17,289 --> 00:09:18,666
開拍
And action.

159
00:09:18,999 --> 00:09:20,793
－那是龍蛋
－這是什麼？
That's a dragon egg.

160
00:09:20,876 --> 00:09:22,419
－就是這樣
－那是什麼？
- What is it? I...
- That's what that is.
- What is that?
- A dragon egg.

161
