The Dark Lord himself forbade me
to speak of this.

1627
01:15:03,565 --> 01:15:05,191
海倫麥柯瑞飾演我的妻子
Helen McCrory played my wife.

1628
01:15:05,609 --> 01:15:09,446
我說過「我認為我遇上
這輩子見過最厲害的女演員了」
I said, "I think I just met the best
actress I've ever seen in my life."

1629
01:15:10,655 --> 01:15:11,698
來
Come.

1630
01:15:11,781 --> 01:15:13,909
我覺得跟她共事很幸運
I feel lucky to have worked with her

1631
01:15:13,992 --> 01:15:18,830
在片場分享
很多年以來缺少的歡笑
and shared just so much

1632
01:15:15,744 --> 01:15:18,747
frankly, adolescent laughter with her
on the set.

1633
01:15:20,624 --> 01:15:22,834
她教了我很多
She had taught me a lot.

1634
01:15:23,668 --> 01:15:24,878
看吧，我連話都說不出來
See, I can't even say it.

1635
01:15:30,258 --> 01:15:32,427
她有種能力可以…
She had this ability, yeah,
just to sort of, to show such empathy

1636
01:15:33,428 --> 01:15:36,640
用雙眼展現同情

1637
01:15:35,722 --> 01:15:37,265
in her eyes.

1638
01:15:37,557 --> 01:15:39,392
跟她合作真的很享受
And it was... the was a real treat
to work with her.

1639
01:15:44,230 --> 01:15:50,654
{\an5}我能教你迷惑頭腦、誘惑感官
I can teach you how to bewitch
the mind and... and snare the senses.

1640
01:15:50,737 --> 01:15:53,740
艾倫瑞克曼跟我說話時
從不把我當小孩
Alan Rickman never talked to me
like I was a child.

1641
01:15:53,823 --> 01:15:58,662
他總是認真對待我的想法和意見
He always took my thoughts
and opinions very seriously

1642
01:15:58,745 --> 01:16:01,331
我一直很感動
which I was always very touched by.

1643
01:16:02,123 --> 01:16:04,042
艾倫生前是我的好朋友
Uh, Alan was a very dear friend
and we had that final scene

1644
01:16:04,125 --> 01:16:06,878
我們一起拍最後一幕
他的最後一幕時

1645
01:16:05,752 --> 01:16:06,878
his final scene.

1646
01:16:08,421 --> 01:16:10,256
那會回應你
It answers to you and you only.

1647
01:16:12,133 --> 01:16:14,219
只有你

1648
01:16:15,095 --> 01:16:16,596
是嗎？
Does it?

1649
01:16:16,680 --> 01:16:19,140
我那時有點怕他
I was a little intimidated by him,
his precision

1650
01:16:19,224 --> 01:16:22,519
他唸台詞的精準專業度

1651
01:16:20,266 --> 01:16:22,519
his expert delivery of lines and...

1652
01:16:22,602 --> 01:16:25,146
我們旗鼓相當得有點搞笑
We sort of went toe to toe,
in a funny way.

1653
01:16:25,230 --> 01:16:26,731
石內卜和佛地魔
You know? Snape and Voldemort.

1654
01:16:26,815 --> 01:16:29,818
兩個演員像擊劍一樣享受共演
Two actors can relish, metaphorically
fencing with each other.

1655
01:16:29,901 --> 01:16:32,487
艾倫身為演員，像個魔術師一樣
Alan was a magician in that way
as an actor.

1656
01:16:38,034 --> 01:16:40,453
愛我們的人從沒離開過
The ones that love us
never really leave us.

1657
01:16:41,997 --> 01:16:43,415
你總能找到他們…
And you can always find them

1658
01:16:46,126 --> 01:16:47,335
就在這裡
in here.

1659
01:16:54,509 --> 01:16:58,138
（摯愛回憶）

1660
01:17:23,538 --> 01:17:24,622
記住
But remember this,...
you're not alone.

1661
01:17:25,999 --> 01:17:27,208
你並不孤單

1662
01:17:32,297 --> 01:17:33,631
接骨木魔杖
The Elder Wand,...
the most powerful wand ever made.

1663
01:17:36,468 --> 01:17:38,887
有史以來最強大的魔杖

1664
01:17:38,970 --> 01:17:41,014
重生石
The Resurrection Stone.

1665
01:17:46,019 --> 01:17:48,646
隱身斗篷
The Cloak of Invisibility.

1666
01:17:50,190 --> 01:17:52,192
這加起來就是死神的聖物
Together they make
the Deathly Hallows.

1667
01:17:52,567 --> 01:17:55,987
加起來就是死神的主人
Together they make one
master of death.

1668
01:17:57,322 --> 01:17:58,740
活下來的男孩
The boy who lived.

1669
01:18:02,202 --> 01:18:03,286
哈利
Harry.

1670
01:18:08,833 --> 01:18:10,043
來受死吧
Come to Papa.

1671
01:18:14,047 --> 01:18:15,548
啊哇呾喀呾啦
Avada Kedavra.

1672
01:18:24,682 --> 01:18:28,728
（丹尼爾雷德克里夫
魯伯特葛林特、艾瑪華生）

1673
01:18:28,812 --> 01:18:32,065
他們對家人採取的保護措施…
The measures they had taken
to protect their families

1674
01:18:32,148 --> 01:18:35,485
讓他了解
他們比任何人能做的更多
made him realize, more than
anything else could have done

1675
01:18:35,568 --> 01:18:38,238
了解伴隨而來的責任
that they really were going to come
with him

1676
01:18:38,321 --> 01:18:41,825
他們確實知道是怎樣的危險
and that they knew exactly
how dangerous that would be.

1677
01:18:41,908 --> 01:18:44,828
他想告訴他們這對他有什麼意義
He wanted to tell them
what that meant to him

1678
01:18:44,911 --> 01:18:48,623
但他就是找不到夠重要的詞語
but he simply could not find words
important enough.

1679
01:18:52,627 --> 01:18:54,879
（第四章，值得爭取的事物）

1680
01:18:54,963 --> 01:18:58,383
（哈利波特
死神的聖物Ｉ、ＩＩ）

1681
01:18:58,466 --> 01:19:03,555
{\an5}在這裡走動感覺很酷又很怪異
It's both really cool
and it's... it is weird

1682
01:19:01,386 --> 01:19:05,723
like, walking around here
and seeing the sets that we were

1683
01:19:03,638 --> 01:19:06,891
{\an5}看到我們小時候的佈景

1684
01:19:05,807 --> 01:19:07,642
like, kids on, who treated everything

1685
01:19:06,975 --> 01:19:08,852
跟兒時看到時的態度完全一樣
with the amount of respect kids
treat things

1686
01:19:08,935 --> 01:19:11,187
我們在現場玩得很開心

1687
01:19:10,061 --> 01:19:11,146
when you're just there
and having fun.

1688
01:19:11,271 --> 01:19:13,273
真的，我感受到一股
詭異的懷舊感
It's weird. I'm having like, weird,
nostalgic moments.

1689
01:19:13,356 --> 01:19:15,441
記得我的倉鼠嗎？
有人記得我的倉鼠嗎？
Do you remember my hamster?
Does anyone remember my hamster.

1690
01:19:15,525 --> 01:19:16,568
－記得
－米莉
- Yes.
- Millie.

1691
01:19:16,651 --> 01:19:17,902
我不記得倉鼠的名字，抱歉
Yeah. I didn't remember
the hamster's name, sorry.

1692
01:19:17,986 --> 01:19:19,195
－對
－沒關係
That's okay. That's okay.
Rest in peace, Millie.

1693
01:19:19,279 --> 01:19:20,572
沒關係，安息吧，米莉

1694
01:19:20,655 --> 01:19:22,115
我記得你有一隻倉鼠
I remember you having a hamster
and being greatly jealous

1695
01:19:22,198 --> 01:19:25,201
我對你在片場有寵物
隱約有點忌妒

1696
01:19:23,241 --> 01:19:25,201
that you had an animal
that was on set with you.

1697
01:19:25,285 --> 01:19:27,704
木工部門替倉鼠
做了棺材，對不對？
They made a coffin for it.

1698
01:19:26,452 --> 01:19:27,537
- They did, yeah.
- The carpentry department.

1699
01:19:27,787 --> 01:19:31,166
米莉死掉時，佈景設計替米莉
- Did they? Jesus.
- When Millie died the set designers

1700
01:19:29,455 --> 01:19:33,793
built Millie her own custom made
wooden coffin

1701
01:19:31,249 --> 01:19:33,793
建造了她客製的木棺材

1702
01:19:33,877 --> 01:19:36,421
－裡面有天鵝絨
－很漂亮
- that had velvet on the inside of it.
- It was beautiful.

1703
01:19:36,504 --> 01:19:41,759
還有刻牠的名字
因為我當時很難過
And, and it had her name engraved.

1704
01:19:38,798 --> 01:19:39,966
- I mean...
- Because I was...

1705
01:19:40,049 --> 01:19:41,759
I mean, I was beside myself.

1706
01:19:41,843 --> 01:19:43,845
我們有辦葬禮嗎？
我覺得我們有致詞過
Did we do like, a service?
I feel like we said a few words.

1707
01:19:43,928 --> 01:19:47,098
我一直想抱起死掉的米莉
I kept wanting to pick up dead
Millie.

1708
01:19:47,182 --> 01:19:49,684
撫摸死掉的米莉
And like, stroke and touch dead
Millie.

1709
01:19:49,767 --> 01:19:54,731
他說
「艾瑪，米莉得待在棺材裡」
And he was like, "Emma, Millie's
gotta stay in the coffin now."

1710
01:19:54,814 --> 01:19:57,192
我都忘了這些事情
I have forgotten so much of this.

1711
01:19:57,275 --> 01:19:59,944
感覺這是沒多久以前的事
It doesn't feel like much time
has passed.

1712
01:20:00,028 --> 01:20:01,237
我知道
- Yeah, I know.
- Yeah.

1713
01:20:01,321 --> 01:20:02,989
我們現在看起來
還是比電影尾聲好
We all still look better than we do
in the epilogue, which is great.

1714
01:20:03,072 --> 01:20:04,157
－這樣很好
－對

1715
01:20:04,240 --> 01:20:05,575
－像我們在那之前辦到的
－這樣很怪
- Which is a win.
- Like, we've made it in before that.

1716
01:20:08,661 --> 01:20:10,246
－袋子呢？
－有帶
- Bag?
- Yeah.

1717
01:20:10,330 --> 01:20:11,956
毛衣呢？
Jumper.

1718
01:20:12,040 --> 01:20:13,666
我那時額頭超高
- Yeah.
- I was all forehead.

1719
01:20:14,125 --> 01:20:15,210
還穿了肥胖裝
- And the fat suit.
- Yeah.

1720
01:20:15,293 --> 01:20:18,046
－對，我很…
－我認為我那時有點…
- I was very... I was... I was...
- I think I kind of...

1721
01:20:18,129 --> 01:20:20,423
你超盡力拍的，你就…
Yeah. You went for it.

1722
01:20:19,130 --> 01:20:20,798
You were like, "Give me the full...

1723
01:20:20,506 --> 01:20:22,050
－給我…
－沒錯，我超盡力拍的
- Give me the suit."
- He went all in.

1724
01:20:22,133 --> 01:20:23,468
－對，你那時全力以赴
－對
- Yeah.
- I was so proud of you.

1725
01:20:23,551 --> 01:20:24,886
我好替你驕傲

1726
01:20:27,138 --> 01:20:29,265
沒人能真正了解
No one else can really quite
understand what we experienced.

1727
01:20:29,349 --> 01:20:31,601
我們的體驗非常獨特
It was a very unique thing.

1728
01:20:31,684 --> 01:20:34,520
大衛葉慈以前說我們是太空人
I think David Yates
used to describe us as astronauts

1729
01:20:34,604 --> 01:20:38,775
因為沒有別人經歷過
這種拍攝規模
because no one else has really
experienced this on this scale

1730
01:20:38,858 --> 01:20:41,277
我們會因此永遠聯繫在一起
and we'll be kind of forever bonded
by that.

1731
01:20:46,574 --> 01:20:48,368
我對我們三個最甜蜜的回憶
Some of the sweetest memories I have
from the three of us

1732
01:20:48,451 --> 01:20:50,954
就是我們都知道，我們必須…
is just each of us knowing we sort of
needed to take care of each other

1733
01:20:51,037 --> 01:20:53,414
用細微的方式照顧彼此

1734
01:20:52,038 --> 01:20:53,665
in just small ways.

1735
01:20:53,498 --> 01:20:57,210
比如說「天氣很冷
我們都要…」
Just in terms of like,
it's really cold.

1736
01:20:55,416 --> 01:20:58,503
Like, we're all gonna st...
We're all gonna stand together.

1737
01:20:57,293 --> 01:20:58,670
「我們要站在一起」

1738
01:20:58,753 --> 01:21:00,421
或者「我累了」
Or, "I'm knackered.

1739
01:21:00,505 --> 01:21:03,383
「丹，我可以靠你身上睡嗎？」
Are you okay, Dan,
if I like, fall asleep on you

1740
01:21:03,466 --> 01:21:06,970
在這兩個鏡頭之間
因為我太累或…
like, in between this take
because I'm so tired?" Or...

1741
01:21:07,053 --> 01:21:11,015
我認為我們都在各種狀況下
靠在彼此身上睡著過
I think we have all fallen asleep
in various

1742
01:21:09,555 --> 01:21:12,642
like, on, on each other in, like,
some of the most grand cathedrals

1743
01:21:11,099 --> 01:21:13,518
在英國幾座最宏偉的大教堂裡

1744
01:21:12,725 --> 01:21:14,310
and things in the UK.

1745
01:21:15,478 --> 01:21:17,605
我的信任程度…
The level of trust that I had

1746
01:21:17,689 --> 01:21:20,275
我們這十年建立的信任
and that we did build
over those 10 years

1747
01:21:20,358 --> 01:21:23,194
我們要是做特技
was like, if we were doing a stunt

1748
01:21:22,110 --> 01:21:25,029
I trusted that one of you
would catch me.

1749
01:21:23,278 --> 01:21:25,029
我信任你們會接住我

1750
01:21:25,113 --> 01:21:27,240
我認為這種信任和依靠
I feel like that kind of trust
and reliance

1751
01:21:27,323 --> 01:21:28,908
這需要…
and that takes... You know,
there's very few work environments

1752
01:21:28,992 --> 01:21:32,078
很少有工作環境
可以讓人建立這種信任程度

1753
01:21:30,576 --> 01:21:31,786
where you get that much time
to build that up.

1754
01:21:32,161 --> 01:21:33,454
而且這些事都不用說出口
And it was like, nonverbal.

1755
01:21:33,538 --> 01:21:37,875
我們三個好像不用說話就能溝通
Like, it was all...
It was like the three of us

1756
01:21:34,789 --> 01:21:37,875
could communicate
without even having to say anything.

1757
01:21:37,959 --> 01:21:39,419
我們就是知道該做的就要做
We just knew what needed to be done.

1758
01:21:39,961 --> 01:21:42,964
我們替彼此保持堅強
We were each very strong
for each other.

1759
01:21:44,382 --> 01:21:45,800
我們得換衣服
I need to change.

1760
01:21:52,348 --> 01:21:53,641
怎麼…
How the ruddy?

1761
01:21:53,725 --> 01:21:55,560
無形伸展咒
Undetectable extension charm.

1762
01:21:56,978 --> 01:21:58,396
你真厲害，真的
You're amazing. You are.

1763
01:21:59,314 --> 01:22:01,441
你總是那麼驚訝
Always the tone of surprise.

1764
01:22:01,524 --> 01:22:03,985
這幾部電影的氛圍很不一樣
These films
had a very different feel.

1765
01:22:04,068 --> 01:22:06,404
我們常常不在霍格華茲
We were away from Hogwarts
a lot of the time

1766
01:22:06,821 --> 01:22:08,364
我們會在不同的地方過夜
camping out in different places.

1767
01:22:08,656 --> 01:22:12,243
氣氛黑暗多了
感覺像不同的電影
Tone was a lot darker,
and it felt like a different film.

1768
01:22:12,327 --> 01:22:14,412
鄧不利多派你去找這些分靈體
Dumbledore sends you off
to find all these Horcruxes

1769
01:22:14,495 --> 01:22:16,164
但他沒叫你摧毀它們
but doesn't tell you
how to destroy them?

1770
01:22:16,247 --> 01:22:18,791
我認為感覺很不一樣
It was very refreshing

1771
01:22:17,332 --> 01:22:21,169
I think, because we all got to do
some a lot more serious stuff

1772
01:22:18,875 --> 01:22:21,294
因為我們都能拍更嚴肅的主題

1773
01:22:21,377 --> 01:22:24,547
有機會更深入
這些角色現實的一面
and it was a real opportunity
to go deeper with these characters.

1774
01:22:24,630 --> 01:22:26,257
你是要來，還是要留下來？
Are you coming, are you staying?

1775
01:22:30,845 --> 01:22:32,472
我那天晚上看到你們兩個
I saw you two the other night.

1776
01:22:33,389 --> 01:22:35,308
榮恩，那…沒什麼
Ron, that's, that's nothing.

1777
01:22:38,019 --> 01:22:39,145
榮恩
Ron.

1778
01:22:40,104 --> 01:22:42,273
我以為會很尷尬的那一幕
The scene that I thought
was gonna be really awkward

1779
01:22:42,357 --> 01:22:43,858
我對那一幕很不確定
and I wasn't sure about at all,
which was us doing our dance.

1780
01:22:43,941 --> 01:22:45,860
那就是我們跳舞那一幕

1781
01:22:45,943 --> 01:22:47,320
－我就…
－對
- Like, I...
- Yeah.

1782
01:22:47,403 --> 01:22:51,115
現在那算我
在整個系列最愛的一幕
Now, that's one of my favorite scenes
from the whole of the series.

1783
01:22:51,574 --> 01:22:55,661
因為我們在那時候
彼此熟悉的程度
Because the level of familiarity

1784
01:22:53,618 --> 01:22:55,411
that you and I had with each other
at that point

1785
01:22:55,745 --> 01:22:58,289
我應該沒辦法
跟另一個演員那樣演
I don't think I could've done a scene
like that with another actor.

1786
01:22:58,373 --> 01:22:59,916
那一幕很有趣的另一個原因
Well, it's also an interesting scene

1787
01:22:59,999 --> 01:23:01,584
因為首先
我們拍的是「哈利波特」
because first of all,
we were doing Harry Potter films

1788
01:23:01,667 --> 01:23:03,753
然後在最後一部電影
導演過來說
and then on the last movie,
the director came in

1789
01:23:03,836 --> 01:23:06,714
「你們聽尼克凱夫的音樂
跳慢舞怎樣？」
and was like, "Hey, how about you do
slow dancing

1790
01:23:05,129 --> 01:23:06,714
to Nick Cave for five minutes?"

1791
01:23:06,798 --> 01:23:08,716
－你說「我們在拍什麼電影？」
－我們說「什麼？」
- Wait, what?
- "Wait, what movie are we working on?

1792
01:23:08,800 --> 01:23:10,218
「好吧」
Like, great, but okay."

1793
01:23:34,242 --> 01:23:37,537
那一幕描述了很多
不言而喻，我很愛那一幕
There's so much unsaid in the scene
